      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I don\u0027t love these instructions either. I went ahead and followed the instructions for getting vpython and they work fine for running the tests.\n\nHowever, none of the other normal dev use cases work well. If we create a link from `run_tests.vpython3` to `.vpython3` (or mv first and then link in reverse order), then running `vpython3` anywhere inside the repo is better, but running `black` or `isort` or any other python-based tool that would respect a venv still doesn\u0027t work as expected because vpython3 doesn\u0027t get invoked.\n\nIf I was making a lot of changes I\u0027d probably try to find a better solution, but for now I guess I\u0027ll use vpython for running tests and pyenv for everything else.",
      "parentUuid": "7ac42377_0a2d0710",
      "revId": "1a9ae3a288655e646595d99f36894ddf516bbc8e",
      "serverId": "173816e5-2b9a-37c3-8a2e-48639d4f1153"
    },
