      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right, and if we added that `.vpython3` file, then you could omit `-vpython-spec run_tests.vpython3`. Beyond that, I think I\u0027d be getting into creating shell functions to look for a `.vypthon3` file or parse the output of `vpython3 -vpython-log-level debug -vpython-tool verify` to see if it found a spec and then either call `vpython3 -m black` or `black`.\n\nIt\u0027d be nice if `vpython3` exposed the venv to activate it, but I guess the whole model doesn\u0027t really support that since you can have per-command and embedded specs.\n\nI\u0027ll abandon this change for now and if it really bugs me in the future I\u0027ll probably add real support for non-vpython tools with a validator script for CI to run to ensure it doesn\u0027t drift from the vpython3 spec.",
